Class ExecutionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.core.ExecutionManager
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndroidExecutionManager

    public class ExecutionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Orchestrator and manager of the other components (Store, Provider, Chooser, Trigger).

      • addTriggerGeneric

        private ExecutionManager addTriggerGeneric(java.lang.String dataKey,
                                           java.lang.String triggerKey,
                                           Trigger trigger,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> map)
        Adds a new Trigger identified by the given triggerKey that operates on the Store identified by the dataKey in the given map. In case another Trigger already exists for the given key, the addition will be aborted.
        Parameters:
        dataKey - the key that identifies the Store observed by the Trigger.
        triggerKey - the key of the Trigger.
        trigger - the trigger to be added.
        map - the map in which the trigger should be put (must be one of triggers or UITriggers.
        Returns:
        the ExecutionManager instance for chaining.
        See Also:
        removeTriggerGeneric(String, Map), addUITrigger(String, String, long, Trigger), addUITrigger(String, String, Trigger), addTrigger(String, String, Trigger)

      • addUITrigger

        public ExecutionManager addUITrigger(java.lang.String dataKey,
                                     java.lang.String triggerKey,
                                     long requestID,
                                     Trigger trigger)
        Adds a new Trigger identified by the given triggerKey that is sensible only to new data from the request identified by the requestID and that operates on the Store identified by the dataKey in UITriggers map. The trigger will be wrapped inside a FilteredTrigger. In case another Trigger already exists for the given key, the addition will be aborted.
        Parameters:
        dataKey - the key that identifies the Store observed by the Trigger.
        triggerKey - the key of the Trigger.
        requestID - the id of the request this Trigger should be observing.
        trigger - the trigger to be added.
        Returns:
        the ExecutionManager instance for chaining.
        See Also:
        FilteredTrigger, addTriggerGeneric(String, String, Trigger, Map), addUITrigger(String, String, Trigger), removeUITrigger(String), removeAllUITriggers()

      • checkStore

        private void checkStore(java.lang.String key,
                        @Nullable
                        java.lang.Class type,
                        boolean autoCreate)
        Checks if a Store for the given key exists and if the data it constains is of the same type of type. If it does not exist and autoCreate is set to true, then it will be created using a new unlimited InMemoryStore.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the store to check.
        type - the type of the data we want to check against.
        autoCreate - if true, the store will be created if not found.
        Throws:
        ExecutionManager.StoreNotDefinedException - thrown if no store is found.
        ExecutionManager.TypeMismatchException - thrown if type is not the same as the Store.getDataType()'
        See Also:
        addStore(String, Store), addProvider(String, String, Provider)

      • addProvider

        public ExecutionManager addProvider(java.lang.String providerKey,
                                    java.lang.String outputKey,
                                    Provider provider)
        Adds a new Provider identified by the given providerKey that provides data identified by the key outputKey. If no Store is found for the given outputKey, a new one will be created as in checkStore(String, Class, boolean).
        Parameters:
        providerKey - the key that identifies the Provider.
        outputKey - the key of the data the Provider provides.
        provider - the Provider to be added.
        Returns:
        the ExecutionManager instance for chaining.
        Throws:
        ExecutionManager.TypeMismatchException - if Store.getDataType() is different from Provider.getInputType().
        See Also:
        removeProvider(String), getProvider(String), checkStore(String, Class, boolean)

      • runProvider

        public void runProvider(java.lang.String providerKey,
                        long request_id,
                        Data... input)
        Runs the Provider identified by the given key.
        Parameters:
        providerKey - the key that identifies the Provider.
        request_id - the id of the request this execution belongs to.
        input - the input data
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if input data is not the same type as Provider.getInputType().
        ExecutionManager.ProviderNotDefinedException - if no provider was found matching the provided key.
        See Also:
        addProvider(String, String, Provider), removeProvider(String), getProvider(String)

      • chooseProvider

        private void chooseProvider(java.util.List<java.lang.String> providers,
                            java.lang.String dataKey,
                            long request_id,
                            Data... input)
        Chooses a Provider to run in the given list. If more than one Provider is given, the right Chooser will be queried to select one of those.
        Parameters:
        providers - the list of providers to choose from.
        dataKey - the key that identifies the data.
        request_id - the id of the request this execution belongs to.
        input - the input data
        Throws:
        ExecutionManager.ChooserNotDefinedException - if there are multiple Providers but no Chooser.
        ExecutionManager.ProviderForDataNotDefinedException - if no provider was found that provides the given data.
        See Also:
        produceData(String, long, Data...), produceDataExcludeProviders(String, long, String[], Data...)

      • produceData

        public void produceData(java.lang.String dataKey,
                        long request_id,
                        Data... input)
        Runs a Provider that produces the data identified by the given key. If more than one Provider is defined, the right Chooser will be queried to select one of those.
        Parameters:
        dataKey - the key that identifies the data.
        request_id - the id of the request this execution belongs to.
        input - the input data
        Throws:
        ExecutionManager.ChooserNotDefinedException - if there are multiple Providers but no Chooser.
        ExecutionManager.ProviderForDataNotDefinedException - if no provider was found that provides the given data.
        See Also:
        chooseProvider(List, String, long, Data...), addProvider(String, String, Provider), removeProvider(String), getProvider(String), produceDataExcludeProviders(String, long, String[], Data...)

      • produceDataExcludeProviders

        public void produceDataExcludeProviders(java.lang.String dataKey,
                                        long request_id,
                                        java.lang.String[] excludedProviders,
                                        Data... input)
        Runs a Provider that produces the data identified by the given key excluding some of the Providers. If more than one Provider is defined and has not been excluded, the right Chooser will be queried to select one of those.
        Parameters:
        dataKey - the key that identifies the data.
        request_id - the id of the request this execution belongs to.
        excludedProviders - providers that must not be run.
        input - the input data
        Throws:
        ExecutionManager.ChooserNotDefinedException - if there are multiple Providers but no Chooser.
        ExecutionManager.ProviderForDataNotDefinedException - if no provider was found that provides the given data.
        See Also:
        chooseProvider(List, String, long, Data...), addProvider(String, String, Provider), removeProvider(String), getProvider(String), produceData(String, long, Data...)
